  m_Name: Intro_LLM_Set_Q5
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::QuestionData
  question: Which of the following best describes a large language model (LLM)?
  answers:
  - It is a specialized networking model that processes data from different sources.
  - It is a database system optimized for handling large volumes of text data.
  - It is a type of machine learning model that processes and generates human-like
    text.
  - It is a software tool used primarily for data encryption.
  maxSelections: 1
  correctAnswerIndices: 02000000
  correctMessage: Large language models are a category of foundational models capable
    of understanding and generating natural language.
  incorrectMessage: Large language models are a category of foundational models capable
    of understanding and generating natural language.
